Description
The VFX Supervisor is responsible for the production of visual effects on the project that is assigned to him. A key consultant of the project s Director, he is responsible for the technical and artistic quality of the shots. The standard of quality is established during his exchanges with the Director and production staff. He must therefore understand and interpret the Director s intentions and also be conscious of the project s budget constraints set by the production team. He works in collaboration with the Post-Production Manager on tasks such as budget, planning and client relations.
Responsibilities
PRE-PRODUCTION:
Prepare the visual effects production breakdown;
Participate in pre-production meetings;
Anticipate problems and present solutions adapted to time and budget constraints;
Recruit and manage pre-production teams, if necessary;
FILMING:
Supervise the filming of VFX sequences: retrieve filming information, oversee the necessary on-set installations for the filming of sequences;
POST-PRODUCTION:
Recruit and manage teams for production;
Maintain communications between the Director and the production team;
Support the coordination team in order to maintain the pipeline s efficiency and allow the artists and TDs to achieve their production objectives and deadlines;
Identify additional tools necessary for production; find and develop solutions in collaboration with the TDs;
Evaluate the utility of new tools/software that are available on the market;
Monitor technological developments;
Qualifications
Minimum five (5) years of work experience as a VFX supervisor in a film production environment, animated TV series or visual effects;
Extensive knowledge of VFX production and CG pipelines;
Thorough understanding of film production and on-set experience;
Experience with recruitment, training and supervision of CG artists;
Knowledge of an asset manager is a plus;
Knowledge of various 2D/3D software (Maya, Nuke, etc.) is a plus;
Excellent organizational and communication skills;
Excellent project management skills;
Ability to supervise and assign tasks to a production team;
Must be attentive to the production team, the other supervisors and the coordinators;
Bilingual (English and Hindi);
Must be willing and able to travel

Description
The CG Supervisor works closely with the VFX Supervisor and the Client to oversee every aspect of production for an commercial/ animated tv series/ feature film. Under the supervision of the Production Manager, he brings expertise to both the technical and artistic aspects of the project while working in collaboration with the various department supervisors. The standard of quality is established during his exchanges with the Director and production staff. He must therefore understand and interpret the Director s intentions and also be conscious of the project s budget constraints set by the production team.
Responsibilities
PROJECT ANALYSIS:
Assist the Production Manager and VFX Supervisor with project proposals;
Work closely with the VFX Supervisor and department supervisors to plan the production based on the budget constraints;
Find relevant information and references to prepare the workload;
Establish the project s quality based on the allotted budget;
Evaluate the technical requirements for the project and the production pipeline; find and propose solutions that are in concordance with the Production Coordinators and the department Supervisors;
MANAGEMENT:
Recruit candidates for key positions in collaboration with the production team;
Provide assistance with the recruitment of 3D Artists to ensure the proper level of skill and experience required for the project;
Prepare the production guidelines and instructions for the Supervisors;
Give clear instructions to each department and set objectives while monitoring the production process, progress and results;
Attend and/or organize and lead production meetings;
Inform the Supervisors on changes and news regarding the projects;
Be available to answer questions from the production team;
Eliminate potential problems with pipeline tools before they affect production;
Assist and participate in client meetings;
PRODUCTION:
During production: develop the production pipeline in collaboration with the VFX Supervisor and Supervisors of each department;
Edit the documentation required for the development of the pipeline;
Keep the documentation intended for the production team and supervisors up to date;
Develop and provide improvements for procedures and tools to maintain an efficient workflow;
Remain attentive to the new technologies available in the in industry and the various production techniques
Remain attentive to emerging technologies and production techniques in the industry and determine how to apply these advances to the current project in order to improve production;
Qualifications
Minimum five (5) years of work experience as a supervisor in a film production environment, animated TV series or visual effects;
Extensive knowledge of any 3D Application(Maya, Blender, Cinema 4D);
Thorough understanding of the various technical and creative aspects of production for CG animation;
Complete understanding of 3D production pipelines;
Knowledge of NUKE is a plus;
Ability to work efficiently with various personalities and different work styles;
Ability to prioritize and work on multiple tasks at a time while remaining efficient and mindful of strict deadlines in a high pressure environment;
Bilingual (English and Hindi)
